  "description": "The American jeremiad is a rhetorical form identified by Sacvan Bercovitch in *The American Jeremiad* (1978). It combines lamentation over present decline with reaffirmation of the community's founding mission, transforming criticism into a ritual of renewal rather than a call for structural change.",
